Through his foundation, JP Duminy has joined forces with Gary Kirsten's project to build a cricket pitch at a school in Khayelitsha. eNCA's Justin Ford has the story. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The COVID-era has perhaps put more spotlight on helping those less fortunate. Sport is no different and it's a challenge former Protea JP Duminy is taking to heart. READ: Chris Morris smashes IPL auction record with $2.25m fee Through his foundation, Duminy has joined forces with Gary Kirsten's project to build a cricket pitch at a school in Khayelitsha. The newly-laid cement pitch will give access and offer opportunities to cricket enthusiasts. Watch the video above for more details on this story.